President Biden delivered a speech in Atlanta, Georgia, emphasizing the importance of protecting voting rights and democracy in the wake of the January 6th insurrection at the U.S. Capitol. He highlighted the historical struggles for civil rights and voting rights, and the ongoing efforts to suppress and subvert elections. Biden called on Congress to pass the Freedom to Vote Act and the John Lewis Voting Rights Advancement Act to combat voter suppression and election subversion. He also expressed support for changing Senate rules to protect voting rights if necessary. The President emphasized that the fight for democracy is not over and urged elected officials to choose the side of justice and the American people.